properties.NAME: Alabama
properties.CHANGE: The state of Alabama was created from Alabama Territory; Alabama Territory eliminated.

properties.NAME: Alabama
properties.CHANGE: Surveyors demarcated the southern segment of the Alabama-Mississippi line, fixing the end point ten miles east of the mouth of the Pascagoula River. BALDWIN, MOBILE, and WASHINGTON lost to the state of Mississippi.

properties.NAME: Alabama
properties.CHANGE: MARION's overlap of the state of Mississippi and TUSCALOOSA's overlap of the state of Mississippi ended.

properties.NAME: Alabama Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Alabama Territory from the eastern half of Mississippi Territory.

properties.NAME: Alabama Territory
properties.CHANGE: TUSCALOOSA created by Alabama Territory from MONTGOMERY and Non-County Area 1; TUSCALOOSA overlapped non-county area in the state of Mississippi.

properties.NAME: Arkansas Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Arkansas Territory from Missouri Territory. Arkansas Territory included all of present Arkansas and part of present Oklahoma. Boundary between Arkansas Territory and Mexico remained unsettled.

properties.NAME: Arkansas Territory
properties.CHANGE: Arkansas Territory was reduced in size when the western extent of the territory was moved to a line running forty miles west of the southwest corner of Missouri.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 4, ch. 155 [1824]/pp. 40-41; Morris, Goins, McReynolds, 21; Van Zandt, 119)

properties.NAME: Arkansas Territory
properties.CHANGE: CLARK, CRAWFORD, LOVELEY, and MILLER lost to Indian lands when the treaty between the United States and Cherokee Indians established the western line of Arkansas Territory north of Red River along the eastern line of the Choctaw Cession.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 7, p. 311; Gabler, 37-39; Royce, 720-721; Van Zandt, 119)

properties.NAME: Connecticut
properties.CHANGE: Connecticut ceded to the United States its claim to lands north and west of Pennsylvania and the Ohio River, except for a tract, lying in the northeast corner of present Ohio, known as the Connecticut Western Reserve.

properties.NAME: Connecticut
properties.CHANGE: Connecticut ceded the Western Reserve in present Ohio to the United States, and the area was incorporated into the Northwest Territory.
properties.CITATION: (Terr. Papers U.S., 3:84-86; U.S. Stat., vol. 2, ch. 38 [1800]/pp. 56-57)

properties.NAME: Connecticut
properties.CHANGE: HARTFORD lost part of the town of Southwick (the "Southwick Jog") to HAMPSHIRE (Mass.) when the state boundary was adjusted.

properties.NAME: District of Columbia
properties.CHANGE: The United States created an unnamed district from land ceded by Maryland and Virginia to be the seat of national government.

properties.NAME: Delaware
properties.CHANGE: The three Lower Counties, of KENT, NEW CASTLE, and SUSSEX became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The name Delaware was formally adopted on 20 September 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: Erie Tri. Unorg. FT
properties.CHANGE: On 29 Oct 1782 New York ceded to the US any claim to territory west of the meridian of the western end of Lake Ontario, thereby defining its western boundary; the Erie Triangle in present Penn. is part of this cession. Map depicts area as of 3 Sep 1783.

properties.NAME: Florida Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created the Territory of Florida from the provinces of East and West Florida ceded by Spain to the United States. The territory had the same boundaries as the present state of Florida.

properties.NAME: Florida Unorg. FT
properties.CHANGE: Spain ceded East Florida and West Florida (i.e., all territory east of the Perdido River) to the United States. Exchange of ratifications was delayed until 21 February 1821.

properties.NAME: Georgia
properties.CHANGE: Georgia became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: Georgia
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Mississippi Territory. Georgia continued to claim this area under its colonial charter, and the federal act said that creation of the territory would not impair Georgia's claim.

properties.NAME: Georgia
properties.CHANGE: Georgia ceded to the United States much of present Mississippi and Alabama. This area became unorganized federal territory and Georgia Western Lands were eliminated.

properties.NAME: Illinois
properties.CHANGE: The state of Illinois was created from Illinois Territory; Illinois Territory eliminated.

properties.NAME: Illinois Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Illinois Territory from Indiana Territory.

properties.NAME: Illinois Territory
properties.CHANGE: The state of Indiana created from Illinois, Indiana, and Michigan Territories; EDWARDS exchanged small areas along the Wabash River with the state of Indiana, establishing the boundary between the present states of Illinois and Indiana.

properties.NAME: Indiana
properties.CHANGE: The state of Indiana was created from Indiana Territory and small parts of Illinois and Michigan Territories.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 3, ch. 57 [1816], secs. 1-2/p. 289 and res. 1 [1816]/p. 399; Van Zandt, 115)

properties.NAME: Indiana Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Indiana Territory from the Northwest Territory; included all of present Illinois and Wisconsin, most of present Indiana, and parts of present Michigan, Minnesota, and Ohio.
properties.CITATION: (Terr. Papers U.S., 3:86-88; U.S. Stat., vol. 2, ch. 41 [1800]/pp. 58-59)

properties.NAME: Indiana Territory
properties.CHANGE: The state of Ohio was created from the Northwest Territory and Indiana Territory. Indiana Territory gained remainder of the former Northwest Territory in present Michigan and Indiana; Northwest Territory eliminated.
properties.CITATION: (Ind. Terr., Exec. Journal, 114-115; Pence and Armstrong, 218; U.S. Stat., vol. 2, ch. 40 [1802], secs. 1-3/pp. 173-174; Van Zandt, 112)

properties.NAME: Indiana Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Michigan Territory from Indiana Territory; WAYNE (Ind. Terr.) was effectively eliminated.
properties.CITATION: (Terr. Papers U.S., 10:5-7; U.S. Stat., vol. 2, ch. 5 [1805]/pp. 309-310; "Territorial Records," 118-121; Blume, 1:2-4)

properties.NAME: Indiana Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Illinois Territory from Indiana Territory.
properties.CITATION: (Terr. Papers U.S., 16:6-8; U.S. Stat., vol. 2, ch. 13 [1809], sec. 1/p. 514)

properties.NAME: Indian Territory
properties.CHANGE: Arkansas Territory was reduced in size when the western extent of the territory was moved to a line running forty miles west of the southwest corner of Missouri. Unorganized federal territory in present Oklahoma became known as Indian Territory.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 4, ch. 155 [1824]/pp. 40-41; Gittinger, 13-17; Morris, Goins, McReynolds, 21; Van Zandt, 119)

properties.NAME: Indian Territory
properties.CHANGE: Indian Territory gained from Arkansas Territory when the Treaty of Washington between the United States and Choctaw Indians definitively established the eastern line of the Choctaw Cession and affirmed Choctaw control of the area west of the line.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 7, p. 311; Gabler, 37-39; Royce, 720-721; Van Zandt, 119)

properties.NAME: Kentucky
properties.CHANGE: The state of Kentucky was created from the Kentucky District of Virginia.

properties.NAME: Dist. of Louisiana
properties.CHANGE: The United States created the District of Louisiana from the part of the Louisiana Purchase north of 33 degrees north latitude, the limit of the present state of Louisiana.
properties.CITATION: (Terr. Papers U.S., 13: 51-52; U.S. Stat., vol. 2, ch. 38 [1804]/pp. 283-289; Violette, 46-47)

properties.NAME: Louisiana Purchase
properties.CHANGE: The United States purchased Louisiana from France, taking formal possession 20 December 1803; boundaries were not clearly defined but unquestionably included the western half of the Mississippi drainage basin.

properties.NAME: Louisiana
properties.CHANGE: The State of Louisiana was created from Orleans Territory; Orleans Territory eliminated.

properties.NAME: Louisiana Territory
properties.CHANGE: District of Louisiana renamed Louisiana Territory and detached from Indiana Territory; the territory included all of present Missouri.

properties.NAME: Massachusetts
properties.CHANGE: Massachusetts, including the area of Maine, became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: Massachusetts
properties.CHANGE: Massachusetts gained part of the town of Southwick (the "Southwick Jog") that lay south of the Connecticut boundary and that had been annexed from Massachusetts in 1774.

properties.NAME: Massachusetts
properties.CHANGE: Maine was separated from Massachusetts and admitted to the Union.

properties.NAME: Maryland
properties.CHANGE: Maryland became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: Maryland
properties.CHANGE: The United States created an unnamed district from land ceded by Maryland and Virginia to be the seat of national government.

properties.NAME: Maine
properties.CHANGE: Maine was separated from Massachusetts and admitted to the Union.

properties.NAME: Michigan Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Michigan Territory from Indiana Territory.
properties.CITATION: (Terr. Papers U.S., 10:5-7; U.S. Stat., vol. 2, ch. 5 [1805]/pp. 309-310)

properties.NAME: Michigan Territory
properties.CHANGE: The state of Indiana was created from Indiana Territory and small parts of Illinois and Michigan Territories.

properties.NAME: Michigan Territory
properties.CHANGE: The state of Illinois was created from Illinois Territory. Michigan Territory gained the former parts of Illinois and Indiana Territories in present Wisconsin and the Upper Peninsula of present Michigan.
properties.CITATION: (Terr. Papers U.S., 10:803; U.S. Stat., vol. 3, ch. 67 [1818], sec. 7/p. 431, and res. 1 [1818]/p. 536)

properties.NAME: Missouri
properties.CHANGE: The state of Missouri was created from Missouri Territory, with all modern boundaries, except for the northwestern corner of the present state, which became unorganized federal territory.

properties.NAME: Missouri Territory
properties.CHANGE: Louisiana Territory renamed Missouri Territory.

properties.NAME: Missouri Territory
properties.CHANGE: Area exchanged with British North America when a Convention of Commerce between Great Britain and the United States established 49 degrees north latitude, from the Lake of the Woods to the Rocky Mtns., as the northern boundary of the United States.

properties.NAME: Missouri Territory
properties.CHANGE: Non-County Area exchanged with Spain as a result of the Adams-Onis Treaty with Spain on 22 February 1819.

properties.NAME: Missouri Territory
properties.CHANGE: HEMPSTEAD created by Missouri Territory from ARKANSAS and non-county area. Uncertainty of boundary between Mexico and the U.S. resulted in competing claims to area in Texas. Act passed 15 December 1818, took effect 1 June 1819.

properties.NAME: Missouri Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Arkansas Territory from that part of Missouri Territory south of the parallel of 36 degrees, 30 minutes north latitude.

properties.NAME: Mississippi
properties.CHANGE: The state of Mississippi was created from Mississippi Territory; Mississippi Territory was eliminated.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 3, ch. 23[1817], secs. 1-2/p. 348 and res. 1[1817]/p. 472; Van Zandt, 105)

properties.NAME: Mississippi
properties.CHANGE: Surveyors demarcated the southern segment of the Alabama-Mississippi line, fixing the end point ten miles east of the mouth of the Pascagoula River.

properties.NAME: Mississippi Terr.
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Mississippi Territory in parts of present Mississippi and Alabama.

properties.NAME: Mississippi Terr.
properties.CHANGE: Mississippi Territory gained unorganized federal territory south of Tennessee (northern portions of present Mississippi and Alabama).

properties.NAME: Mississippi Terr.
properties.CHANGE: The state of Louisiana was created from Orleans Territory; Orleans Territory eliminated. The area encompassed by PASCAGOULA (Orleans Terr.) was formally added to Mississippi Territory on 14 May 1812.

properties.NAME: Mississippi Terr.
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Alabama Territory from the eastern half of Mississippi Territory.

properties.NAME: North Carolina
properties.CHANGE: North Carolina became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: North Carolina
properties.CHANGE: Congress accepted North Carolina's cession of its western lands (i.e. present Tennessee).

properties.NAME: New Hampshire
properties.CHANGE: New Hampshire became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: New Jersey
properties.CHANGE: New Jersey became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: Northwest Territory
properties.CHANGE: The U.S. created the Territory of the United States Northwest of the River Ohio (Northwest Territory) from unorganized federal territory.

properties.NAME: Northwest Territory
properties.CHANGE: WASHINGTON created by the Northwest Territory from non-county area and part of the Western Reserve. This implicit challenge to Connecticut's authority in the Western Reserve went unanswered.
properties.CITATION: (Terr. Papers U.S., 3:278-279; Chase, 3:ch. 330/p. 2096; Cappon, Petchenik, and Long, 92)

properties.NAME: Northwest Territory
properties.CHANGE: WAYNE (Northwest Terr., extinct) created by the Northwest Territory from HAMILTON (Ohio), KNOX (Ind.), and non-county area.

properties.NAME: Northwest Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Indiana Territory from the Northwest Territory; included all of present Illinois and Wisconsin, most of present Indiana, and parts of present Michigan, Minnesota, and Ohio.
properties.CITATION: (Terr. Papers U.S., 3:86-88; U.S. Stat., vol. 2, ch. 41 [1800]/pp. 58-59)

properties.NAME: New York
properties.CHANGE: New York became an independent state on 4 July 1776, and Vermont declared its independence from New York on 15 January 1777. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: Ohio
properties.CHANGE: The state of Ohio was created from the Northwest Territory and Indiana Territory.
properties.CITATION: (Ind. Terr., Exec. Journal, 114-115; Pence and Armstrong, 218; U.S. Stat., vol. 2, ch. 40 [1802], secs. 1-3/pp. 173-174; Van Zandt, 112)

properties.NAME: Orleans Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created Orleans Territory from that portion of Louisiana south of the parallel of 33 degrees north latitude, west of the Mississippi River, and south of Mississippi Territory east of the river.
properties.CITATION: (Terr. Papers U.S., 13: 51-52; U.S. Stat., vol. 2, ch. 38 [1804]/pp. 283-289; Van Zandt, 107; Violette, 46-47)

properties.NAME: Oregon Country
properties.CHANGE: Based on American exploration of the Northwest, the United States claimed the Oregon Country, an area west of the 1803 Louisiana Purchase that was not specifically defined.

properties.NAME: Pennsylvania
properties.CHANGE: Pennsylvania became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: Pennsylvania
properties.CHANGE: Pennsylvania purchased from the federal government the Erie Triangle, a small area immediately north of Pennsylvania and west of New York, giving Pennsylvania an outlet to Lake Erie.

properties.NAME: Rhode Island
properties.CHANGE: Rhode Island became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: South Carolina
properties.CHANGE: South Carolina became an independent state on 4 July 1776. The map depicts state boundaries as of 3 September 1783.

properties.NAME: Southwest Territory
properties.CHANGE: The United States created the Territory of the United States South of the River Ohio (Southwest Territory), covering the territory ceded in April 1790 by North Carolina (area of present Tennessee).
properties.CITATION: (Terr. Papers U.S., 4:18-19; U.S. Stat., vol. 1, ch. 14[1790], p. 123)

properties.NAME: Tennessee
properties.CHANGE: The state of Tennessee was created from the Territory of the United States South of the River Ohio (Southwest Territory); Southwest Territory eliminated.
properties.CITATION: (U.S. Stat., vol. 1, ch. 47[1796], pp. 491-492; Folmsbee, Corlew, and Mitchell 110)

properties.NAME: Uncert. Bound. Area
properties.CHANGE: The boundary from Lake of the Woods to the Rocky Mtns. between the United States and the British possessions was unsettled.

properties.NAME: Unorg. Fed. Terr.
properties.CHANGE: Congress accepted North Carolina's cession of its western lands (i.e. present Tennessee).

properties.NAME: Unorg. Fed. Terr.
properties.CHANGE: Georgia ceded to the United States all territory south of North Carolina and Tennessee, east of the Mississippi River, north of 31 degrees north latitude and west of the present limit of Georgia. The area became unorganized federal territory.

properties.NAME: Unorg. Fed. Terr.
properties.CHANGE: Part of the Upper Peninsula of present Michigan and the extreme eastern part of present Wisconsin became unorganized federal territory when the state of Indiana was created from Indiana, Illinois, and Michigan Territories.

properties.NAME: Unorg. Fed. Terr.
properties.CHANGE: The state of Missouri was created from part of Missouri Territory; Missouri Territory eliminated and all that part of the former territory north and west of the state of Missouri became unorganized federal territory.

properties.NAME: Unorg. Fed. Terr.
properties.CHANGE: The unorganized federal territory lost to the creation of Indian Territory.

properties.NAME: Virginia
properties.CHANGE: Virginia ceded to the United States its 1609 charter claims to territory "northwestward of the river Ohio," thereby setting the north bank of the Ohio River as the northern and northwestern limit for present Kentucky and West Virginia.

properties.NAME: Virginia
properties.CHANGE: The United States created an unnamed federal district (now the District of Columbia) from MONTGOMERY and PRINCE GEORGES in Maryland and from FAIRFAX in Virginia to be the seat of the federal government.

properties.NAME: Virginia
properties.CHANGE: The state of Kentucky was created from the Kentucky District of Virginia.

properties.NAME: Vermont Republic
properties.CHANGE: Vermont declared its independence from New York in 1777. Although not recognized as a separate state by the Continental Congress, Vermont functioned as an independent republic until statehood in 1791. Map depicts Vermont boundaries as of 3 Sep 1783.
properties.CITATION: (Slade, 70-73; Van Zandt, 64; Williamson, C., 82-84, map facing 95, 100-102, 112-113)

properties.NAME: Vermont
properties.CHANGE: The state of Vermont was admitted to the Union. The boundary with New York was settled by a joint commission before statehood.
